'''Mike Edwards''' is an [[American football]] player who was most recently a [[cornerback]] for the [[Hawaii Warriors football|Hawaii Warriors]] of the [[University of Hawaii]]. In 2012, he led the nation in [[Kickoff (gridiron football)|kickoff]] return yards.

==High school==
Edwards attended [[Glenville High School]] in [[Cleveland|Cleveland, Ohio]], and was a member of the school's football and track teams. He helped the football team win a regional title and a state championship. As a senior, he had 34 [[Tackle (football move)|tackles]] and five [[interception]]s and was named to the All-State first team.<ref name="Hawaii">[http://hawaiiathletics.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=11456 "Mike Edwards"]. hawaiiathletics.com. Retrieved February 7, 2013.</ref><ref>[http://www.utsports.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/edwards_mike00.html "Mike Edwards"]. utsports.com. Retrieved February 7, 2013.</ref>

==College==
Edwards played for the [[Tennessee Volunteers football|University of Tennessee]] in 2009. He appeared in eight games and had five tackles. He then redshirted the 2010 season at [[Coffeyville Community College]].<ref name="Hawaii"/>

In 2011, Edwards went to the University of Hawaii and started 12 games at cornerback. He had 43 tackles that season. He also had 44 kick returns, and his 24.7 yard average was second-best in the [[Western Athletic Conference|WAC]].<ref name="Hawaii"/>

In 2012, Edwards led the nation with 1,215 kickoff return yards and had a 30.4 yard average.<ref name="draft">[http://www.hawaiiathletics.com/news/2013/1/2/FB_0102130716.aspx "Mike Edwards To Forgo Senior Season"]. hawaiiathletics.com. January 2, 2013. Retrieved February 7, 2013.</ref> His three kickoff returns for [[touchdown]]s set a Hawaii single-season record. Edwards also had 43 tackles. He was named the [[Mountain West Conference]]'s Special Teams Player of the Year. After the season, Edwards entered the [[National Football League Draft|NFL Draft]]. He finished his career at Hawaii with 2,301 total kickoff return yards, which was a school record.<ref name="draft"/>

==Personal==
Edwards was born in Cleveland, Ohio, to Mike and Tameeka Edwards. He has one brother, two sisters, and two sons. Edwards is a sociology major. He is 5 feet, 10 inches tall, and weighs 180 pounds.<ref name="Hawaii"/><ref>[http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/sports/college/football/wac/hawaii/notes/49831372/1 "Hawaii Team Notes"]. usatoday30.usatoday.com. December 12, 2012. Retrieved February 7, 2013.</ref>

After his freshman season at Tennessee, Edwards and some of his teammates held up some people with a pellet gun. He was charged with three counts of attempted armed robbery. He pleaded down to a lesser charge and was sentenced to two years probation.<ref>Reardon, Dave. [http://www.staradvertiser.com/columnists/20110204_Recruit_will_get_second_chance_at_UH__its_what_we_do.html?id=115262569 "Recruit will get second chance at UH <U+2014> it's what we do"]. staradvertiser.com. February 4, 2011. Retrieved February 7, 2013.</ref>

